product_name: MaybellineFit Me Matte + Poreless Liquid Foundation
summary: SummaryMaybelline Fit Me Matte + Poreless Foundation goes beyond skin tone matching to fit the unique texture issues of normal to oily skin. Lightweight. Oil-free.
details: DetailsBenefitsProvides oil-free, medium coverage with a natural matte and poreless-looking finishUltra-breathable and lightweight, it absorbs oil, controls shine and won't clog poresCreated in many shades so you can always find your perfect fit with 12 hour lasting wearFeaturesFormulated with clay for normal to oily skinFragrance-freeNon-comedogenicDermatologist tested and allergy-testedItem 2282913How To UseApply foundation onto skin and blend with fingertips or an applicator.Precautions: Flammable until dry. Do not use near fire, flame, or heat.IngredientsAqua/Water/Eau, Cyclohexasiloxane, Nylon-12, Isododecane, Alcohol Denat., Cyclopentasiloxane, Peg-10 Dimethicone, Cetyl Peg/Ppg-10/1 Dimethicone, Peg-20, Polyglyceryl-4 Isostearate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Phenoxyethanol, Magnesium Sulfate, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, HDI/Trimethylol Hexyllactone Crosspolymer, Titanium Dioxide, Methylparaben, Acrylates Copolymer, Tocopherol, Butylparaben, Aluminum Hydroxide, Alumina, Silica, Glycerin. May Contain: CI 77891/Titanium Dioxide, CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499/Iron Oxides, D166390/3.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsShipping Restrictions : This item cannot be shipped via air.
how_to_use: Apply foundation onto skin and blend with fingertips or an applicator.Precautions: Flammable until dry. Do not use near fire, flame, or heat.

reviews.headline: I wouldn't buy this
reviews.comments: Product was too light for my skin tone, didn't blend in well.

reviews.headline: Ehhhhhh
reviews.comments: It's okay for spot covering and maybe some discoloration. I've tried a bare face and super dewy face and it wears the same no matter what I do to the skin on my face. You can see blend marks with a brush and it separates easily on the forehead.

reviews.headline: Great coverage for oily & acne prone skin!
reviews.comments: This works really well especially for oily and acne prone skin! I use a damp real techniques orange sponge and the coverage is perfect!

reviews.headline: I would not by this again
reviews.comments: I bought this foundation to try it out and it was awful. It left my skin flakey. It also did not blend properly and was clumpy.  I don't recommend buying this foundation

reviews.headline: Perfect Foundation
reviews.comments: This foundation is perfect for giving the glowy, smooth look. This goes on lightweight and a dab goes a long way.

reviews.headline: Still the One
reviews.comments: After trying dozens of other foundations, I found myself coming back to Maybe Fit Me once again! The coverage is perfectly buildable, lasts all day and I finally found my perfect match color.

reviews.headline: Acne prone safe !
reviews.comments: I have severe acne prone/ hormonal skin. i have acne scars, active acne, really un even skin tone,  skin texture, and i am really insecure about it. I've probably been using this foundation since i was 17 and i am 20 years old now. I have switched back and fourth between high end brands and drug store brands nothing else preforms and blends and covers better then this foundation for me. I want to mention that i have practiced the art of covering up my acne for awhile so in my own opinion i think i am really bomb at my OWN makeup routine and i have learned how to apply foundation the way my skin needs it to be applied and not everyone is going to be the same. I apply foundation with a brush, it has way more coverage and does not take the foundation with it like a beauty blender would. I used to use a beauty blender when i had clear skin it still preformed seamlessly for me but with having acne and all that a beauty blender is actually my worst enemy. I also want to add, i color correct my face like crazy so i think thats also why my foundation looks amazing once applied. I do have combo skin and all i use to prep is a moisturizer and sunscreen. thats it. I don't get active breakouts from this foundation. my top 3 reasons why i use this and always will unless my skin starts to clear up anytime soon. I highly recommend this if you have skin problems like me ! only thing i hate obviously is that there is no pump. I wish they would add that but other then that this is the best for me!!

reviews.headline: So good.
reviews.comments: I've really been struggling to find a foundation that I absolutely enjoy ok my skin. From trying so many high end brands to finally ending up here with this one. It's so. gooooood. Worth every penny. Gives the skin a naturally flawless look (filter who?), wore well in high humidity and heat, easy to apply, doesn't settle into fine lines or emphasize dry patches. Easily a 10/10 for me in every aspect, I'll be repurchasing in the future.

reviews.headline: Greasy Mess
reviews.comments: Destroyed my skin. Water based but feels like a layer of straight oil. I had clear skin before this product; after using, I've developed a red rash and bumps on the apples of my cheeks. Easily cakey and creates texture. Overall, not worth the damage

reviews.headline: Yes yes
reviews.comments: I've been trying to see what foundation can work for oily skin that can be affordable for a daily wear. I also have large pores and texture on my skin. Finding a good match can be hard especially if you have different areas you want to cover. Would I recommend it yes, it doesn't sink in your pores and it blends well. No patches it does not crease. But it will get on your clothes, it is not waterproof, and it didn't help keep my face matte over an hr.

reviews.headline: looks like im wearing no foundation
reviews.comments: i put it all over my face but it looks like theres nothing on. it matches my skin so well and blends really easily into skin

reviews.headline: Very good for oily skin and if you want natural coverage
reviews.comments: This is an excellent affordable foundation that leaves a natural medium coverage for those who have oily skin. Doesn't look cakey and its buildable. The powder and concealer all work very well together. Would definitely recommend for oily skinned girlies.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I have loved Fit Me since I was introduced to it in Oct 2016. All the women in my family use it and it's a wonderful product. 

However,  when I purchased the product this month I was a little concerned about the pigment of the 110. It had more yellow undertones than the previous month. This works out because my skin happens to be kind of olive but definitely concerned me. I attached the swatches and the bottles to prove they are the same. The left is the new bottle and right is the old. When the foundation is exposed to oxygen does it lose pigment? 

This won't keep me from buying the product in the future and still love what I've got! It just was noticeably different.
faceoff_positive.headline: Love this product but Theres a catch

faceoff_negative.comments: I bought this around 3-4 months ago because my bestfriend raved about it and I'm just starting off in makeup so this was inexpensive and apparently so great color wise. The first time I applied it, it was beautiful, so matte so perfect. I went out and got oily as expected but great. The second time and third time and fourth time, it felt heavy, felt cakey, it oxidized HARD, which I saw coming but it was to a point that I felt like an Oompa Loompa after the first time. Idk maybe I got a bad one because my bestfriend still loves her, but for me being real oil skin and having lots of pores I was a sucker for this one and I loved it, THE FIRST time. But then idk fell flat. Maybe it was one bottle
faceoff_negative.headline: Weird
